            <title>[SPARK-14187] Incorrect use of binarysearch in SparseMatrix</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-14187</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;SparseMatrix&lt;/tt&gt; use binarySearch to find &lt;tt&gt;index&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;binarySearch returns index of the search key, if it is contained in the array within the specified range; otherwise, (-(insertion point) - 1).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On the other hand, &lt;tt&gt;update&lt;/tt&gt; method only compare the returned index with -1 to decide whether it is found or not.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
